South African manufacturing growth
probably slowed to 3 percent in June from 4.2 percent in the
previous month, according to the median estimate of eight
economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  Statistics  South Africa  is due to publish the data at 1
p.m. in Pretoria, the capital.  (All events in Central African Time.) 